explanation: This solution iterates over the string s to find all occurrences of string a. For each occurrence, it iterates over the string s again to find all occurrences of string b within a certain distance. The indices of beautiful strings are added to the result list and sorted at the end. The time complexity is O(n^2) due to the nested loops, and the space complexity is O(n) for storing the result list.

